<plot>This Passing Parade short dramatizes the events surrounding the first invasive surgical operation performed in the United States, performed by Dr. Ephraim McDowell on December 13, 1809. Jane Crawford of Danville, Kentucky is diagnosed with a tumor and Dr. McDowell determines that surgery is the only treatment option. The townsfolk are against this and threaten to lynch him if he goes through with it.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?411909</url></doc>
